    <header>
        <h1><marquee behavior="alternate" ;bgcolor="blue" ;height="1000">Prawn Masala</marquee></h1>
    </header>

    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>1 lb large prawns, peeled and deveined</li>
            <li>1 cup onion, finely chopped</li>
            <li>1 cup tomatoes, pureed</li>
            <li>1/4 cup vegetable oil</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon ginger-garlic paste</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon turmeric powder</li>
            <li>2 teaspoons red chili powder</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon coriander powder</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon garam masala</li>
            <li>Salt to taste</li>
            <li>Fresh cilantro for garnish</li>
            <li>Lemon wedges for serving</li>
        </ul>
    </section>
    <section>
        <h2>Tags</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>nonveg</li>
            <li>indian</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>In a pan, heat vegetable oil over medium heat. Add chopped onions and sauté until golden brown.</li>
            <li>Add ginger-garlic paste and sauté until the raw smell disappears.</li>
            <li>Add turmeric powder, red chili powder, coriander powder, and garam masala. Stir well to combine.</li>
            <li>Add pureed tomatoes and cook until the oil separates from the masala.</li>
            <li>Add the peeled and deveined prawns. Cook until they turn opaque and are cooked through.</li>
            <li>Season with salt and garnish with fresh cilantro.</li>
            <li>Serve hot with steamed rice or naan.</li>
            <li>Enjoy your flavorful Prawn Masala!</li>
        </ol>
    </section>
